overview: The immensely gifted singer-songwriter/producer JMSN is debuting a film screening of his “Live North Hollywood” set at the MA Lounge & Theatre in Los Angeles.  The eight-track live recording holds some of the Michigan native’s most treasured compositions (mostly from his last release It Is), revealing a multitude of musical talents. From singing and producing to playing the drums and guitar, JMSN is truly a one-man band, one who has lent his talents to artists such as Kendrick Lamar, The Game, Ab-Soul, Freddie Gibbs, and The Weeknd.  Recorded at Big Bang Studios in North Hollywood and featuring a stellar live band,
title: JMSN: Live North Hollywood
